[{"id":"VH925884","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Assume a competitive firm is producing where price <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, P, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, P, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>(P)</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and marginal revenue <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, M R, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, M R, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>MR</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are greater than marginal cost <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, M C, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, M C, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>MC</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and average variable cost <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, A V C, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, A V C, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>AVC</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following is true regarding the firmâ€™s short-run output level?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH925884_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The firm is producing too little and should increase its output level until <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P equals M R, which equals M C\"><math alttext=\"P equals M R, which equals M C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>P = </mtext><mtext>MR</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>MC</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The firm is producing too much and should reduce its output level until <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-